      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "It's hard to knock the form of ROWEINER'S DANCE (3) who has three wins and a second from his past four starts and again gets the benefit of a 2kg claimer in the irons. Should be able to dictate terms from the favourable draw and is sure to be right there when the whips are cracking. RUSSIAN MINT (6) has three wins and a placing from four attempts over this track and trip and will be high on confidence following back-to-back victories. Gets in light and has to be included in calculations. LEAN EAGLE (7) resumes here but the form he showed when last in work was good enough to play a major role in this contest. Can run a race while fresh. The well-related TURBEAU (5) (half to G3 winner and 2xG2 placed Thames Court) is first-up but has a handy fresh record and should be hitting the line with gusto. SPEED LEGEND (1) rounds out the selections.",
